<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><refentry version="5.0-subset Scilab" xml:id="imbwselect" xml:lang="en" xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><refnamediv><refname>imbwselect</refname><refpurpose>Select components using seed coordinates.</refpurpose></refnamediv><refsynopsisdiv><title>Syntax</title><synopsis>selected = imbwselect(image, x, y); selected = imbwselect(image, x, y, connectivity)</synopsis></refsynopsisdiv><refsection><title>Parameters</title><variablelist><varlistentry><term>image</term><listitem><para>Binary or numeric 2D image.</para></listitem></varlistentry><varlistentry><term>x, y</term><listitem><para>Matching one-based column and row seed coordinates.</para></listitem></varlistentry><varlistentry><term>connectivity</term><listitem><para>4 or 8. The default is 8.</para></listitem></varlistentry><varlistentry><term>selected</term><listitem><para>Boolean mask containing components that contain at least one seed.</para></listitem></varlistentry></variablelist></refsection><refsection><title>Description</title><para><function>imbwselect</function> selects complete connected components containing the requested seeds. Interactive point selection is intentionally not performed.</para></refsection><refsection><title>Examples</title><programlisting><![CDATA[mask = zeros(7, 7) == 1; mask(2:3, 2:3) = %t; selected = imbwselect(mask, 2, 2);]]></programlisting></refsection><refsection role="see also"><title>See also</title><simplelist type="inline"><member><link linkend="imconnectedcomponents">imconnectedcomponents</link></member><member><link linkend="imconnectedcomponents">imconnectedcomponents</link></member></simplelist></refsection><refsection><title>Authors</title><simplelist type="vert"><member>Tan Chin Luh</member></simplelist></refsection><refsection><title>History</title><informaltable border="1"><tr><td>Version</td><td>Description</td></tr><tr><td>5.0.0</td><td>Function introduced in development Step 3.</td></tr></informaltable></refsection></refentry>
